---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
layout: "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
---
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Grim Gatherings - About</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="src/assets/favicon.png" type="image/x-icon" />

    <style>
      body {
        background-color: rgb(82, 81, 81);
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-family: 'Franklin Gothic Medium', 'Arial Narrow', Arial, sans-serif;
      }

      header, footer {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      #container {
        color: white;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0;
        background-color: black;
        max-width: 1200px;
        text-align: center;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
      }

      #container img {
        max-width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }

      p {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        line-height: 1.4;
        margin-top: 0.5rem;
        padding: 0 0.5rem;
      }

      h3{
        font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
        color: #6BF933
      }

      footer {
        background-color: #333;
        color: white;
        padding: 0.5rem;
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: auto;
      }

      header {
        background-color: #333;
        padding: 0.5rem;
      }

      @media (max-width: 768px) {
        #container {
          padding: 0.5rem;
        }

        p {
          font-size: 1rem;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header />
    
    <div id="container">
      <div>
        <img src="src/assets/about-banner.png" alt="About Banner" />
      </div>

      <p>
        Welcome to <span style="color: #FF2200;">Grim Gatherings</span> – THE event site for those who embrace the darker side of life. 
        Created for those with a love for the gothic, the gritty, and the unapologetically unpolished.

        At Grim Gatherings, we provide a site where those who live for the grim and the raw can come together. If you’ve ever felt out of place in a sea of pastel perfection, or tired of the sanitized, "clean" vibe of most social spaces, you’ve found your tribe. 
        Whether you’re drawn to the haunting rhythms of metal and grunge or the dimly lit charm of dive bars, this is where you can find events that make you feel like you belong.

        Here, we celebrate the unconventional and the misunderstood, offering events and places to connect with others who share your love for the darker, more authentic things in life.
      </p>

      <h3> Welcome to your gathering of kindred spirits! </h3>
    </div>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>